# {{alias}} - Moru Sandbox Template

This is a Moru sandbox template that allows you to run code in a controlled environment.

## Prerequisites

Before you begin, make sure you have:
- A Moru account (sign up at [moru.io](https://moru.io))
- Your Moru API key (get it from your [Moru dashboard](https://moru.io/dashboard))
{{#if isTypeScript}}- Node.js and npm/yarn (or similar) installed{{else if isPython}}- Python installed{{/if}}

## Configuration

1. Create a `.env` file in your project root or set the environment variable:
   ```
   MORU_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
   ```

## Installing Dependencies

```bash
{{#if isTypeScript}}
npm install @moru-ai/core
{{else if isPython}}
pip install moru
{{/if}}
```

## Building the Template

```bash
{{#if isTypeScript}}
# For development
npm run moru:build:dev

# For production
npm run moru:build:prod
{{else if isPython}}
# For development
make moru:build:dev

# For production
make moru:build:prod
{{/if}}
```

## Using the Template in a Sandbox

Once your template is built, you can use it in your Moru sandbox:

{{#if isTypeScript}}
```typescript
import { Sandbox } from '@moru-ai/core'

// Create a new sandbox instance
const sandbox = await Sandbox.create('{{alias}}')

// Your sandbox is ready to use!
console.log('Sandbox created successfully')
```
{{else if isPythonSync}}
```python
from moru import Sandbox

# Create a new sandbox instance
sandbox = Sandbox.create('{{alias}}')

# Your sandbox is ready to use!
print('Sandbox created successfully')
```
{{else if isPythonAsync}}
```python
from moru import AsyncSandbox
import asyncio

async def main():
    # Create a new sandbox instance
    sandbox = await AsyncSandbox.create('{{alias}}')

    # Your sandbox is ready to use!
    print('Sandbox created successfully')

# Run the async function
asyncio.run(main())
```
{{/if}}

